<quiz>
    <question>
        <prompt>The Equal Rights Amendment (ERA) faced opposition from:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Male politicians exclusively</option>
            <option letter="b">Women's groups concerned about protective legislation</option>
            <option letter="c">Religious organizations only</option>
            <option letter="d">Corporate interests</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>The ERA, proposed in 1923, faced significant opposition from women's groups and labor organizations who feared it would eliminate protective legislation for working women. Groups like the Women's Trade Union League worried that the amendment's absolute equality would invalidate laws setting maximum hours and minimum wages for women workers, highlighting divisions within the women's movement over equality versus protection.</explanation>
    </question>
</quiz>
